  buffer += "\n\n\n<div class=\"card\">\n	<h3>Oxford University Security<span class=\"strapline\">Delivering safety and security through effective prevention, reassurance and response</span></h3>\n	<div class=\"padded-contents\">\n		<p>We have compiled the following advice to help keep you safe and secure whilst in Oxford. We recommend that after reading that you register your valuables .</p>\n	</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"card padded-card\" id=\"register-items\">\n	<h3>1. Register/track your belongings</h3>\n	<div class=\"padded-contents\">\n		<h4>Register laptops, phones etc</h4>\n		<p>We recommend you register these items at <a href=\"https://www.immobilise.com\" title=\"Immobilise\" target=\"_blank\"><i class=\"fa fa-external-link\"></i> Immobilise</a> which is a national database of items accessible to law enforcement which will be cross referenced when stolen goods have been found or recovered.</p>\n\n		<h4>Register cycles</h4>\n		<p>Contact <a href=\"tel:+441865272944\" title=\"Call University security\"><i class=\"fa fa-phone\"></i> University security</a> and ask us about marking your bike with a unique code that ensures that the Police will be able to trace your bike back to you if it is stolen and recovered.</p>\n\n		<h4>Tracking your computer or phone</h4>\n		<p>There are a number of tracking apps available, we recommend using <a href=\"http://preyproject.com/\" title=\"Prey mobile phone tracking app\" target=\"_blank\"><i class=\"fa fa-external-link\"></i> Prey</a> which will use your device's GPS or WiFi to locate it and can even photograph your thief using the device's camera. If you're using an Apple device <a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/gb/app/find-my-iphone/id376101648?mt=8\" title=\"Find my iPhone on the App Store\" target=\"_blank\"><i class=\"fa fa-external-link\"></i> Find my iPhone</a> will help you track and <em>disable/wipe</em> your lost devices (works for most Apple devices, not just iPhones).</p>\n	</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"card\">\n	<h3>2. Personal Safety</h3>\n	<div class=\"padded-contents\">\n		<p>The following helps you think about your own personal situation and to take responsibilities for your safety in your surroundings.</p>\n		<ul>\n			<li>Report incidents of suspicious packages, people or anything else security related to <a href=\"tel:+441865272944\" title=\"Call University security\"><i class=\"fa fa-phone\"></i> University security</a></li>\n			<li>If you are witnessing a crime taking place around the University call the <a href=\"tel:+441865289999\" title=\"Call University security emergency\"><i class=\"fa fa-phone\"></i> University security emergency number</a> or call the Police on 112.</li>\n			<li>Never let people know passwords to your computers or online services.</li>\n			<li>Don't divulge your banking PIN numbers to anyone, even your friends.</li>\n			<li>Please don't wedge doors open that are locked or require fob/swipe access.</li>\n		</ul>\n		<h4>Out and about</h4>\n		<ul>\n			<li>Never carry large sums of money or passports with you unless you really need to.</li>\n			<li>If you're wearing headphones, please wear only one as this will keep you alert to your surroundings.</li>\n			<li>Always try to stay in a group if out at night.</li>\n			<li>If you do walk home <em>don't</em> take shortcuts, stay where it is lit and where plenty of people or cars will be passing.</li>\n			<li>If someone grabs your bag let them have it as it's better to lose a bag than get injured.</li>\n		</ul>\n		<h4>If you think you are being followed</h4>\n		<ul>\n			<li>Walk with confidence, don't look at the ground. Most opportunist offenders will pick on someone that looks vulnerable and not someone who is confident.</li>\n			<li>Keep looking behind you, so the person knows that you cannot be surprised.</li>\n			<li>Cross the streete and/or change direction.</li>\n			<li>If you are on the University estate call <a href=\"tel:+441865289999\" title=\"Call University security emergency\"><i class=\"fa fa-phone\"></i> University security emergency number</a>.</li>\n		</ul>\n	</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"card\">\n	<h3>3. Security</h3>\n	<div class=\"padded-contents\">\n		<h4>Cycles</h4>\n		<p>Unfortunately cycle crime does happen around the University estate, follow these simple tips to keep help your cycle safe.</p>\n		<ul>\n			<li>Always use a D Lock which is \"<a href=\"http://www.soldsecure.com/\" title=\"Sold Secure's website\" target=\"_blank\"><i class=\"fa fa-external-link\"></i> Sold Secure</a>\". These locks have been tested and are sold as \"Bronze\", \"Silver\" and \"Gold\" which correspond to an attack resistance of 1, 3 or 5 minutes.</li>\n			<li>When parking your bike remove any lights, use locking wheel nuts on your wheels and remove the saddle if portable.</li>\n			<li>Always lock your bike to cycle hoops or in a secure cycle storage area.</li>\n			<li>Don't buy an expensive bike just to ride to University.</li>\n		</ul>\n		<h4>Belongings in accomodation</h4>\n		<ul>\n			<li><a href=\"#register-items\" title=\"Jump to the register items section\">Register your belongings</a></li>\n			<li>Don't leave laptops or mobile phones in view of open windows, it takes seconds to reach in from the street to grab something.</li>\n			<li>Question people trying to get into a house or college hall if you don't recognise them, tailgating is a frequent event in Universities.</li>\n			<li>If living in private accomodation, don't always assume that people are friends of friends - they could be opportunists waiting to get into a student house to take laptops, money, phones.</li>\n			<li>Backup your work to an external drive that's kept separately to your computer so if the worst happens, at least you will have your work!</li>\n		</ul>\n	</div>\n</div>\n\n</div>\n";
